08:30.260 --> 08:32.680
So the way that React works is it has commits, right?

08:32.680 --> 08:34.160
So they're basically like packets

08:34.160 --> 08:35.560
of things that have changed.

08:36.580 --> 08:38.020
And you can see what caused the update,

08:38.020 --> 08:40.780
how long it took, what the priority was,

08:40.780 --> 08:43.300
because you can have deferred and immediate updates.

08:43.300 --> 08:45.860
There's all sorts of fun stuff you can do.

08:45.860 --> 08:47.140
We're not talking about performance

08:47.140 --> 08:48.860
so much in this particular course.

08:48.860 --> 08:51.140
